BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:AHGFAMILY-evl0muys3i3r-20250216T154148
DTSTAMP;TZID=UTC:20240708T192251
LAST-MODIFIED;TZID=UTC:20250216T154148
SUMMARY:Timber Derby Race Day
DESCRIPTION: Since we can't call it a Pinewood Derby due to copyright 
 laws, we've decided to adopt the name of " Timber Derby ". No matter what 
 you call it, it's a lot of fun! Design your car, cut it, sand it smooth, 
 paint it, put the wheels on and then it's time to RACE! The race is open 
 to all registered youth, but guests are welcome to come cheer on the 
 racers. Be sure to read and understand our official rules. Though we 
 don't want to disqualify anyone, we do need to stick to the rules to make 
 the race fair for everyone. Anyone not meeting the rules will be put into 
 an "Outlaw" class. They will still be allowed to race, but will not 
 qualify for a trophy. The "Outlaw" class will only be restricted by the 
 overall size and weight limits in the official rules. CHECK IN will start 
 at 9:15 and run until 10:15. The RACE will start promptly at 10:30. Make 
 sure you have checked your car in by 10:15 to be able to race. Late 
 entries will not be allowed. All racers must check their cars in with 
 race staff. Once a car has been weighed and fully checked in, it will be 
 placed in the staging area until the race. Modifications to cars are only 
 allowed before they are fully checked in. After they have been checked 
 in, no modifications can be made. Mechanical failures during the race 
 will be assessed on an individual basis, and repairs may be allowed. Time 
 limits for repairs and post-repair inspections will be up to the race 
 officials. Uniforms are REQUIRED for all registered youth who are racing. 
 There will be a small concession stand available for purchasing 
 refreshments. We need donations of small, individually wrapped items to 
 be able to sell. The proceeds will go toward troop funds to help with our 
 operating expenses. Please remember that we have individuals with nut and 
 other allergies, so NO NUTS OR BEANS (including things like Humus). We 
 can use things like chips, cookies, juice boxes, water bottles, fruit, 
 etc. Home made items are fine, but please bring a label to identify the 
 item with a list of ingredients. We will also have pizza available for 
 purchase. Please see Bryan with any questions or concerns. We can't wait 
 to see you there. Good Luck! NY2911 Timber Derby Official Rules 
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN""><BODY><p>Since we can't call it a Pinewood <span class="il">Derby</span> due to copyright laws, we've decided to adopt the name of "<span class="il">Timber</span> <span class="il">Derby</span>". No matter what you call it, it's a lot of fun! Design your car, cut it, sand it smooth, paint it, put the wheels on and then it's time to RACE! The race is open to all registered youth, but guests are welcome to come cheer on the racers. Be sure to read and understand our official rules. Though we don't want to disqualify anyone, we do need to stick to the rules to make the race fair for everyone.</p><p>Anyone not meeting the rules will be put into an "Outlaw" class. They will still be allowed to race, but will not qualify for a trophy. The "Outlaw" class will only be restricted by the overall size and weight limits in the official rules.</p><p>CHECK IN will start at 9:15 and run until 10:15. The RACE will start promptly at 10:30. Make sure you have checked your car in by 10:15 to be able to race. Late entries will not be allowed.</p><p>All racers must check their cars in with race staff. Once a car has been weighed and fully checked in, it will be placed in the staging area until the race. Modifications to cars are only allowed before they are fully checked in. After they have been checked in, no modifications can be made. Mechanical failures during the race will be assessed on an individual basis, and repairs may be allowed. Time limits for repairs and post-repair inspections will be up to the race officials.</p><p>Uniforms are REQUIRED for all registered youth who are racing.</p><p>There will be a small concession stand available for purchasing refreshments. We need donations of small, individually wrapped items to be able to sell. The proceeds will go toward troop funds to help with our operating expenses. Please remember that we have individuals with nut and other allergies, so NO NUTS OR BEANS (including things like Humus). We can use things like chips, cookies, juice boxes, water bottles, fruit, etc. Home made items are fine, but please bring a label to identify the item with a list of ingredients. We will also have pizza available for purchase.<br /></p><p>Please see Bryan with any questions or concerns. We can't wait to see you there. Good Luck!</p><p><a href="https://www.ahgfamily.org/getdoc/doceffjhmyiu">NY2911 Timber Derby Official Rules</a></p></BODY></HTML>
