SUMMARY:PiPa Lock in & CPR Class
DESCRIPTION: A night of fun and games for the PiPa Level. ( this includes 
 explorers that leveled up at the end of year ceremony) The cost will be 
 $30. $25 is for the cpr class (the troop is covering $10 from this yrs 
 dues total cost of $35 per person) and then the normal $5 breakfast food 
 fee for the overnight. Friday night we will start off with a CPR course. 
 the girls will be fully certified by the end. This is part of their 
 Emergency Preparedness badge we have been working on here and there. This 
 course is the reason for the increase in cost for the lock in. If you 
 would like to come for the cpr class but not stay the night that is fine. 
 Payment is due by the end of yr ceremony 
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN""><BODY><p>A night of fun and games for the PiPa Level. ( this includes explorers that leveled up at the end of year ceremony)</p><p>The cost will be $30. $25 is for the cpr class (the troop is covering $10 from this yrs dues total cost of $35 per person) and then the normal $5 breakfast food fee for the overnight. </p><p>Friday night we will start off with a CPR course. the girls will be fully certified by the end. This is part of their Emergency Preparedness badge we have been working on here and there. This course is the reason for the increase in cost for the lock in.</p><p>If you would like to come for the cpr class but not stay the night that is fine.</p><p>Payment is due by the end of yr ceremony </p></BODY></HTML>
DTSTART;TZID=UTC:20250530T220000
DTEND;TZID=UTC:20250531T150000
