END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:AHGFAMILY-evihluzoeyio-20250621T232023
DTSTAMP;TZID=UTC:20240709T165019
LAST-MODIFIED;TZID=UTC:20250621T232023
SUMMARY:June Campout
DESCRIPTION: Join us for our first campout of the summer. We will be 
 working on the orienteering part of the geocaching and orienteering 
 badge. Tenderhearts require an adult member parent to be with them on any 
 overnights. If you need to register to be able to come please let me know 
 sooner than later as the process can take a couple weeks to complete. We 
 will meet at the campsite at 6pm Friday evening. There will only be a 
 snack provided Friday night so please make sure to eat dinner before 
 coming . Let me know of any food allergies or medications for kids I will 
 need to be aware of for the weekend. All medications need to be turned 
 into me at drop off. Close toed shoes are required for the weekend. bring 
 your mess kits and weather appropriate cloths. as well as light weight 
 long pants and long sleeve shirt for our hike/badgework time, as the area 
 has tick activity and full coverage is the best way to prevent bites. 
 pack Sleeping bags pillows and sleeping mats and extra blankets you may 
 need Rain gear in case a towel in case you get wet for any reason We do 
 have some troop tents for the explorer level and Pipa's to use, but 
 tenderhearts tent with their parents so you should have your own tents. 
 let me know if you need to use a troop tent though we can make sure you 
 have what you need for the weekend. Cost is $25 per person. Payment will 
 be due by the end of year ceremony for in person payment, or you can mail 
 me a check after that due by the Monday before the campout 6/23 Pick up 
 is at 10 am Sunday morning. 
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN""><BODY><p>Join us for our first campout of the summer. We will be working on the orienteering part of the geocaching and orienteering badge. </p><p>Tenderhearts require an adult member parent to be with them on any overnights. If you need to register to be able to come please let me know sooner than later as the process can take a couple weeks to complete.</p><p>We will meet at the campsite at 6pm Friday evening. There will only be a snack provided Friday night so please make sure to <strong>eat dinner before coming</strong>.</p><p>Let me know of any food allergies or medications for kids I will need to be aware of for the weekend. All medications need to be turned into me at drop off.</p><p>Close toed shoes are required for the weekend. </p><p>bring your mess kits and weather appropriate cloths. as well as light weight long pants and long sleeve shirt for our hike/badgework time, as the area has tick activity and full coverage is the best way to prevent bites.</p><p>pack Sleeping bags pillows and sleeping mats and extra blankets you may need</p><p>Rain gear in case</p><p>a towel in case you get wet for any reason</p><p>We do have some troop tents for the explorer level and Pipa's to use, but tenderhearts tent with their parents so you should have your own tents. let me know if you need to use a troop tent though we can make sure you have what you need for the weekend.</p><p>Cost is $25 per person. Payment will be due by the end of year ceremony for in person payment, or you can mail me a check after that due by the Monday before the campout 6/23</p><p>Pick up is at 10 am Sunday morning.</p></BODY></HTML>
