BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:AHGFAMILY-evh3u8nw9y69-20260319T013628
DTSTAMP;TZID=UTC:20250729T142401
LAST-MODIFIED;TZID=UTC:20260319T013628
SUMMARY:Timber Derby
DESCRIPTION: Help us as part of the race crew (mostly adult roles, some 
 available to youth):  
 https://www.signupgenius.com/go/10C0C45A9AD29A3F4C43-62712680-2026 Since 
 we can't call it a Pinewood Derby due to copyright laws, we've decided to 
 adopt the name of "Timber Derby". No matter what you call it, it's a lot 
 of fun! Design your car, cut it, sand it smooth, paint it, put the wheels 
 on and then it's time to RACE! The race is open to all registered youth, 
 but guests are welcome to come cheer on the racers. Be sure to read and 
 understand our official rules. Though we don't want to disqualify anyone, 
 we do need to stick to the rules to make the race fair for everyone. 
 Anyone not meeting the rules will be put into an "Outlaw" class. They 
 will still be allowed to race, but will not qualify for a trophy. The 
 "Outlaw" class will only be restricted by the overall size and weight 
 limits in the official rules.  ​Adults can participate as "Outlaws" 
 this year. CHECK IN will start at 9:15 and run until 10:15. The RACE will 
 start promptly at 10:30. Make sure you have checked your car in by 10:15 
 to be able to race. Late entries will not be allowed. All racers must 
 check their cars in with race staff. Once a car has been weighed and 
 fully checked in, it will be placed in the staging area until the race. 
 Modifications to cars are only allowed before they are fully checked in. 
 After they have been checked in, no modifications can be made. Mechanical 
 failures during the race will be assessed on an individual basis, and 
 repairs may be allowed. Time limits for repairs and post-repair 
 inspections will be up to the race officials. Uniforms are REQUIRED for 
 all registered youth who are racing. There will be a small concession 
 stand available for purchasing refreshments. We need donations of small, 
 individually wrapped items to be able to sell. The proceeds will go 
 toward the awards for the race. Please remember that we have individuals 
 with nut and other allergies, so NO NUTS OR BEANS (including things like 
 Humus) . We can use things like chips, cookies, juice boxes, water 
 bottles, fruit, etc. Home made items are fine, but please bring a label 
 to identify the item with a list of ingredients. We will also have pizza 
 available for purchase. Please see Bryan with any questions or concerns. 
 We can't wait to see you there. Good Luck! NY2911 Timber Derby Official 
 Rules 
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN""><BODY><p><strong>Help us as part of the race crew (mostly adult roles, some available to youth): <a href="https://www.signupgenius.com/go/10C0C45A9AD29A3F4C43-62712680-2026" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">https://www.signupgenius.com/go/10C0C45A9AD29A3F4C43-62712680-2026</a></strong></p> <p>Since we can't call it a Pinewood Derby due to copyright laws, we've decided to adopt the name of "Timber Derby". No matter what you call it, it's a lot of fun! Design your car, cut it, sand it smooth, paint it, put the wheels on and then it's time to RACE! The race is open to all registered youth, but guests are welcome to come cheer on the racers. Be sure to read and understand our official rules. Though we don't want to disqualify anyone, we do need to stick to the rules to make the race fair for everyone.</p> <p>Anyone not meeting the rules will be put into an "Outlaw" class. They will still be allowed to race, but will not qualify for a trophy. The "Outlaw" class will only be restricted by the overall size and weight limits in the official rules. <strong>​Adults can participate as "Outlaws" this year.</strong></p> <p>CHECK IN will start at 9:15 and run until 10:15. The RACE will start promptly at 10:30. Make sure you have checked your car in by 10:15 to be able to race. Late entries will not be allowed.</p> <p>All racers must check their cars in with race staff. Once a car has been weighed and fully checked in, it will be placed in the staging area until the race. Modifications to cars are only allowed before they are fully checked in. After they have been checked in, no modifications can be made. Mechanical failures during the race will be assessed on an individual basis, and repairs may be allowed. Time limits for repairs and post-repair inspections will be up to the race officials.</p> <p>Uniforms are REQUIRED for all registered youth who are racing.</p> <p>There will be a small concession stand available for purchasing refreshments. We need donations of small, individually wrapped items to be able to sell. The proceeds will go toward the awards for the race. Please remember that we have individuals with nut and other allergies, so <strong>NO NUTS OR BEANS (including things like Humus)</strong>. We can use things like chips, cookies, juice boxes, water bottles, fruit, etc. Home made items are fine, but please bring a label to identify the item with a list of ingredients. We will also have pizza available for purchase.<br /></p> <p>Please see Bryan with any questions or concerns. We can't wait to see you there. Good Luck!</p> <p><a href="https://www.traillifeconnect.com/getdoc/doci1ceaojdg" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">NY2911 Timber Derby Official Rules</a></p></BODY></HTML>
